function copyToStorage(VotingSystemStorageLib.VotingToken[] memory votingTokens, VotingSystemStorageLib.VotingToken[] storage storageVotingTokens) public {
    for (uint256 i = 0; i < votingTokens.length; i++) {
        storageVotingTokens.push(votingTokens[i]);
    }
}
```

In the above example, we use a loop to iterate through each element of the `votingTokens` array and push it to the `storageVotingTokens` array. This way, each element of the memory array will be individually copied to storage.

Note that this approach assumes that the `storageVotingTokens` array is initially empty, as it uses `push()` to add elements to the storage array. If the storage array already contains data, you may need to modify the code accordingly to append the elements instead of pushing them.

